For visual detection mode, as shown in Fig. 4
                        a & b, the UV-vis spectra at 652 nm during H2O2 concentration dependent (from 0 M to 0.1 M) phenomenon, while Cu(II)-LPQDs reacted with H2O2-TMB mixture. Among them, the detection limit of H2O2 reaches 80 nM, which is lower than the previous works (Table 2
                        ) [42–51]. In fluorescence detection mode, Fig. 4c & d show the change in fluorescence intensity at different H2O2 concentrations (0 M to 0.4 M). The detection limit of H2O2 using fluorescence mode is as low as 2.5 μM.
